f a sudden he flashed a glance at me and said:

“If I took a trip to Italy, I’d indeed paint some gorgeous stuff. What I’d get out of selling it, would at once go to settle my debt.”

“Your debt? Got debts?” I asked mockingly.

“Oh, drop it, Hermann Karlovich,” said he, using for the first time, I think, my name and patronymic. “You quite understand what I’m driving at. Lend me two hundred fifty marks, or make it dollars, and I’ll pray for your soul in all the Florentine ch